## Appendix B: Oscillation-Stage Readout: Detailed Design

### B.1 Balanced Homodyne Detection

Basic setup:

```
Signal ─────┬─────> Photodiode 1 ──┐
            │                       ├──> Subtraction ──> ADC
LO ─────────┴─────> Photodiode 2 ──┘
```

Local oscillator (LO) is phase-locked to master laser.

Photocurrents:

$$i_1 \propto |E_s + E_{LO}|^2 = |E_s|^2 + |E_{LO}|^2 + 2|E_s||E_{LO}|\cos(\phi)$$

$$i_2 \propto |E_s - E_{LO}|^2 = |E_s|^2 + |E_{LO}|^2 - 2|E_s||E_{LO}|\cos(\phi)$$

Difference:

$$i_1 - i_2 \propto 4|E_s||E_{LO}|\cos(\phi)$$

This is proportional to the **in-phase component** of the signal.

By varying the LO phase by 90°, we get the **quadrature component**, recovering full complex amplitude:

$$E_s = |E_s|e^{i\phi} \to (I, Q) \to (\text{amplitude}, \text{phase})$$

### B.2 Phase-to-Symbol Mapping

Once we have $\phi \in [0, 2\pi)$, map to digital symbols:

**QPSK (2 bits):**
```
Quadrant I   (0° to 90°):    00
Quadrant II  (90° to 180°):  01
Quadrant III (180° to 270°): 11
Quadrant IV  (270° to 360°): 10
```

**8-PSK (3 bits):**
```
Region 0 (0° to 45°):     000
Region 1 (45° to 90°):    001
Region 2 (90° to 135°):   011
...
Region 7 (315° to 360°):  100
```

ADC samples I and Q values, firmware determines which region, outputs bits.

---

## Appendix C: Fabrication Platform Comparison

| Platform | Advantages | Disadvantages | KbLS Suitability |
|----------|------------|---------------|------------------|
| Silicon Photonics | CMOS compatible, mature, high integration | Thermal sensitivity, 2-photon absorption at telecom | **High** — best for passive core |
| Silicon Nitride | Lower loss, no TPA, wider transparency | Less mature, harder to integrate electronics | **Medium** — good for low-loss rings |
| InP | Direct bandgap, active components integrated | Expensive, smaller wafers, less mature foundries | **Medium** — good for lasers, SOAs |
| Lithium Niobate | Excellent electro-optic, low loss | Difficult to pattern, expensive | **Low** — good for modulators only |
| Hybrid | Best of each platform | Complex assembly, alignment challenges | **High** — likely best long-term solution |

**KbLS recommendation:** Start with silicon photonics for compute core, hybrid integrate InP laser and SOA.

